BT /F2 13 Tf 0.08 0.20 0.32 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 724.00 Tm (2:13:51 - Basics Data Modeling) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 700.00 Tm ([GUIDE] :\) Data modeling ang backbone ng dashboard. Kapag mali ang relationship ng tables,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 686.00 Tm (kahit maganda ang chart, mali pa rin ang numbers. Pretty dashboard plus wrong data equals) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 672.00 Tm (dangerous dashboard.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 653.00 Tm (Data modeling is organizing data into tables/entities and defining relationships between them.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 639.00 Tm (Sa BI, magandang data model ang foundation ng reliable dashboard.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 620.00 Tm ([TERMS] Important terms:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 606.00 Tm (- Entity: object or concept represented by a table, e.g. Customer, Product, Order.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 592.00 Tm (- Fact table: table with events/transactions and numeric measures, e.g. Orders.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 578.00 Tm (- Dimension table: descriptive table, e.g. Customers, Products.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 564.00 Tm (- Star schema: one fact table in center connected to dimension tables.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 550.00 Tm (- Snowflake schema: dimension tables are further normalized into related tables.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 536.00 Tm (- Cardinality: relationship count, e.g. one-to-many, many-to-one.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 517.00 Tm ([EXAMPLE] -> Practical example: Orders is fact table. Customers and Products are dimensions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 503.00 Tm (Orders connect to Customers via Customer ID and to Products via Product ID.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 484.00 Tm ([TAKEAWAY] = Summary: Good data modeling prevents wrong numbers and makes analysis easier.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 0.08 0.20 0.32 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 458.00 Tm (2:19:57 - Logical & Physical Layers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 434.00 Tm ([GUIDE] :\) Ito ang isa sa concepts na dapat dahan-dahan. Logical layer is about meaning and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 420.00 Tm (relationships; physical layer is about actual merging of tables. Magkaiba ang effect nila sa) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 406.00 Tm (results.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 387.00 Tm (Tableau data model has two layers:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 373.00 Tm (- Logical layer: default layer where tables are connected using relationships. Tables stay) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 359.00 Tm (  separate.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 345.00 Tm (- Physical layer: inside a logical table, where you can use joins and unions. Tables can be) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 331.00 Tm (  merged.) Tj ET
BT /F2 10.2 Tf 0 0 0 rg 1 0 0 1 54.00 312.00 Tm ([TERMS] Important terms:) Tj ET
